            "label": "Description of Program",
            "help_text": "Detailed description of the program and why it is being requested.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* This $9 billion request funds NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD), ensuring continued U.S. leadership in space exploration and scientific discovery.\n* NASA Science directly supports CT-05's industrial base, including a $177,299 contract with Ensign-Bickford Aerospace & Defense in Simsbury for specialized spacecraft deployment hardware.\n* SMD investment secures American competitiveness against rising space ambitions from China and ensures the stability of the high-tech workforce and domestic supply chains.\n* Funding supports peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities, advancing critical research in planetary defense, climate monitoring, and the search for life beyond Earth.",
            "rationale": "The description identifies the $9B ask for SMD and links it to specific CT-05 economic activity via Ensign-Bickford Aerospace & Defense. It incorporates key advocacy themes regarding U.S. leadership, competition with China, and the importance of Decadal Survey priorities as mentioned in the reference values.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
